entries.femaleVariant: Inside! Quick!
Just in time for dinner!
Phew... I need to catch my breath…
What is this – heatstroke?! Get back here!
Not hungry. I just swallowed a pound of sand.
Looks like we're in for the night.
A little power might be useful.
Right.
Anything else, Your Excellency?
Now come here! I have a surprise for you!
Right. Gimme a sec.
Anything else, Your Excellency?
Hey, it worked! We have lights!
Huh, I'll need to think about it. Though it'll be the end of our friendship if Saul freezes to death.
Could you help me look, V? I'll search in here.
Thank you. If Saul freezes to death, it will have been a wasted day.
That Wraiths crap... It shouldn't have happened. They wanted everything – our camp locations, routes, offloading points...
If they knew what state we're in… one or two more raids and that'd be the end of us.
And if you hadn't mounted a raid of your own, well... that would have been the end of me.
See that? Clenched teeth, furrowed brow – it's his way of saying "thanks."
We've had our spats.
A few. Like any family.
They're not worth digging up.
I think so too.
If you'd like to come back... Everyone'll be waiting, arms open wide.
But there will have to be changes. No more jumpin' to the front of the line.
And so it begins…
You know what's comin'? Bigger fucking problems. Maybe a war.
We can't hope to handle the Raffens alone.
So you would sell us out to Biotechnica?
V, tell him it's a damn rotten idea!
But right now... I wouldn't mind catching a few winks.
Need help?
Fuck off.
Huh... Do you know what they call these storms in North Africa?
Haboobs.
Damn, I love that word.
Damn, it's getting cold…
I tried to get us some heat in here, but no luck.
Go on, get off your feet. It could be hours.
No, no lecture.
But we do need to talk.
See what I see?
Expiration date's from before the last war, so hopefully it hasn't turned to poison.
Today's our lucky day.
"Lucky..." Interesting choice of words.
Do I hear a lecture coming on?
Prolly just the meds.
Whoa, what was that about?
To haboobs.
Yeeaaah…
To haboobs!
Prolly the meds talkin'.
I sure hope so. I think he took a few solid hits to his skull.
Gotta agree with Panam. Sounds like a truly shitty idea.
entries.maleVariant: I gotta agree with Panam. Sounds like a truly shitty idea.

entries.femaleVariant: Thanks.
What could you possibly know about it?
If you're gonna bloody the furniture, keep me out of it.
Don't be mad, but... I think Saul could be right.
What?! Why?
Eh, not the time for this. You're both exhausted.
entries.maleVariant: Hehh, it's not the time for this. You're both exhausted.

entries.femaleVariant: Clan survival – that's what's at stake.
Sometimes you gotta join with the strong.
Biotechnica mostly plays a clean game. Got a fighting chance with them.
Forget I said anything.
Rather not follow in the Bakkers' footsteps.
'Bout freedom? Quite a bit, actually.
Worked for corpos. Know how this'll end.
Forget I said anything.
Y'know, forget I said anything.
'Member the Bakkers?
I'm a bit hazy…
Exactly. Joined up with Snake Nation, then poof – evaporated.
entries.maleVariant: Exactly. Joined up with the Snake Nation, then poof – evaporated.

entries.femaleVariant: Aldecaldos' strength's always been their independence.
entries.maleVariant: Aldecaldos' strength has always been their independence.

entries.femaleVariant: Give that up, my clan's fate will be yours. Or worse. 'Cause Biotechnica just ain't Snake Nation.
Know what I always liked about nomads? Your taste, no – hunger for freedom.
entries.maleVariant: Y'know what I always liked about nomads? Your taste, uh, no – your hunger for freedom.

entries.femaleVariant: Not easy to come by in Night City. The corps got their grubby claws in everything.
entries.maleVariant: It's not easy to come by in Night City. The corps got their grubby claws in everything.

entries.femaleVariant: And I just can't believe you'd hand them what you hold to be most precious.
More than you think, Saul. Used to work for Arasaka. So, seen plenty.
Arasaka's not Biotechnica. The difference--
Is not in the MO – that's always the same. Know what you are to them?
entries.maleVariant: Is not in the MO – that's always the same. Y'know what you are to them?

entries.femaleVariant: Labor.
To be exploited and ultimately consumed. Best case scenario.
Clan's future, its survival – that's what's at stake.
entries.maleVariant: The clan's future, its survival – that's what's at stake.

entries.femaleVariant: Mhm. Did you hear me talking about something else?
Compared the Raffens to locusts. I mean, Biotechnica's got experience with pests.
Know how things work in Night City?
entries.maleVariant: Y'know how things work in Night City?

entries.femaleVariant: Got everybody fightin' for a slice of the street. If you keep gettin' jumped, you find some stronger choombas.
entries.maleVariant: You got everybody fightin' for a slice of the street. If you keep gettin' jumped, you find some stronger choombas.

entries.femaleVariant: You're talking about gangs.
Principles're the same out here. Oughta remember that.
entries.maleVariant: The principles're the same out here. You oughta remember that.

entries.femaleVariant: I hear teeth grinding? That's fair.
entries.maleVariant: I hear teeth grinding. That's fair.

entries.femaleVariant: But that's how things stand. The stronger survive.
Biotechnica plays a fair game, mostly. Snug under their wing, you might just have a chance.
entries.maleVariant: Biotechnica plays a fair game, mostly. You snug under their wing, you might just have a chance.

entries.femaleVariant: Thank you, V. I could not have said it better.
Hear that, Panam? That is the voice of reason.
All I hear is the fucking wind.
Maybe you're right.
You know what, sweetheart? We'll have plenty of time to tear at each other's throats later.
That is my hope.
Haha, funny...
What is?
I rarely sleep with a roof overhead, yet this will be the second time with you.
When you're on the road day into night into day, your butt basically fusing with your seat, you forget what it's like.
Ma'am, I'm sure you'd be cozier with your shoes off.
Haha, after a full day in them? I'd fear a health code violation.
Nonsense, after a day as full as today, you deserve to kick back.
Oh? And what did you have in mind?
Uh, ahem, V...
No.
It's really nice as is. Let's not spoil it, OK?
How's your whiskey, ma'am?
Hmm... Pff, warm... subtle metallic aftertaste.
Bold, yet smooth. Four out of five stars.
Grumpy guy at reception is the one thing missing.
[Touch Panam's thigh] Got a few ideas.
You choose. Customer's always right.
A good, long sleep.
Got a few ideas…
Think you know what kind.
We deserve a good, long sleep.
Right, so... friends, then.
Sorry. Don't know what I was thinking.
Right.
So... friends, then?
V… I'm glad you came. Really, thanks.
I think that would be best.
And V... I am glad you came.
It meant a lot to me.
Uaugh... Do you hear that...?
Uhh... nope?
Hmph. Mhm. The wind has waned.
I can't speak for haboobs, but… when a chinook rolls rough and rowdy across the plain, hehh, I sure can't get any shuteye…
Not a wink.
On behalf of the staff of the Independent California Motel…
I wish you all sweet dreams.
I-I... I'm, I'm sorry, I... I dunno what I was thinking...
entries.maleVariant: Yea-I, buhh... I-I'm sorry... Dunno what I was thinking...

entries.femaleVariant: Oh, it's fine, truly. Don't let it worry you.
Here at the Independent California, customer satisfaction is job one.
Your wish is our command...
You'd be more comfortable with your shoes off, ma'am.
Think I'm ready to turn it in for the night.
How's your whiskey?
Huhh, think I'm ready to turn in.
Yeah, it's been a long day.
And? This any better?
Hard to get used to.
And? Think this is any better?
entries.maleVariant: And? You think this is any better?

entries.femaleVariant: No... just different.
Tell me about it... I'm still not used to it.
entries.maleVariant: Tell me about it, heh... I'm still not used to it.

entries.femaleVariant: Right?
Yeah, this would make for a decent little motel, wouldn't it? Little fireplace, booze…
Maybe getting a bit too comfortable?
Sure you're not getting too comfortable?
Umm...
Forgot myself a bit, huh?
Maybe a little.
You know what? We better get some sleep. That was a damn long day.
Yeah, prime. Sell us your land or...
A lot of useful things. The Ingalls left in a hurry.
Let's take it easy – you're both tired.
[Sit]
[Raise a toast] To haboobs.
What are you thinking? These storms are no joke!
It your aim to drive into that devil?! Cut the crap!
[Adjust fuse]
Actually, you know what? Check the fuse outside, it might have come loose.
Can you check it? Might have the magic touch.
Hey, we got it! It's cozier already!
If so, just whack it back in place and I'll get this junk burning.
Pleased with your stay, ma'am?
Have everything you need, ma'am?
Oh, yeah…
Mmhmm... I couldn't ask for more.
Biotechnica made them a good offer.
No bulldozers, no backhoe loaders ever showed up. Lousy, rotten way to get them out.
You don't know that.
Deal with a corp, you end with nothing, Saul.
Don't go there, not now.
Careful, you can't know what I'd wish for…
I would settle for a soft pillow.
Hmm?
Might prove hard to come by.
We'll see.
Don't be angry, but Saul has a point.
Shitty idea, Panam's right.
Don't drag me into this.
[Get out]
